FORELHOST — THE LABORATORY (Section 5), THE FIGHT
=====================================================================
- Opened on initiative at the freeze: trap sprung, Alfonso's body unmade by the
  sterilization field, his soul in the corroded rapier on the cage floor under
  his own Stabilized ice; the extraction arm could not reach it (machine drew
  nothing — Antoine lost his backup sample). False Draugr deploying.

- ISMARA AT THE WHEEL. Davinia's player was late (childcare); by table agreement
  Ismara played Davinia until she arrived. CDI did NOT advance — a cost-free loan,
  ruled as a kindness, not a Sovereign's Domain integration-check. Ismara took ~one
  turn and one-shot a False Draugr with a special attack (cold/Aegis — doubled
  against it). When the player returned, Ismara handed the wheel back graciously and
  receded. PRECEDENT NOW SET: the party has met Ismara as a person who can drive and
  converse, and she gave it back like a gift.

- THE FALSE DRAUGR WERE UNDER-TIERED. Saijah hits ~50 in a single shot vs their 35
  HP, so they were one-shot and the regen/control design never engaged. REBALANCE
  PENDING (logged in GM Guide/False Draugr Reference): bump HP ~60-70 and/or DR, or
  re-pitch as a pure control swarm; tune to the AP~12 party. Party cleared/held them.

- SAIJAH PICKED UP THE RAPIER. Auto-infected on contact (Hircine will burn it out —
  feverish a day, then fine). The borrowed-body link engaged: Alfonso, Wakeful, could
  act through her and speak into her mind. (First live use of the new Sentient Sword
  Sec. III rules — Stage 0 Bearing, no Tenancy risk in one fight.)

- THE TWO SOUL-VESSELS SPOKE. Alfonso addressed Ismara; Ismara answered — the marquee
  meeting of the two souls that live in objects. She named what no one else can see:
  the Crown of Namira is pooling toward his rapier; the hand holding him is "borrowing
  trouble" (the Tenancy she can perceive and he cannot); and she does not understand
  why he refuses to re-embody. A rare un-strategic beat for her — "good, after four
  thousand years, to not be the only one in the room who lives in a thing."

- THE ISMARA CURE-PROJECT LAUNCHED (new ongoing thread). Davinia's player chose to
  let Ismara turn her researcher's mind to curing the Forelhost Strain in Davinia.
  Approach is structural, not divine: NOT Restoration (the Strain feeds on it) — come
  from entropy/VENITAS, with Alfonso as collaborator, Antoine's notes as literature,
  and Saijah's Hircine-purge as a data point. (RP notes prepared for the player; see
  also the dependency undertext — letting Ismara solve the body's survival is the
  reflex she cultivates.)

- Alfonso STAYED A SWORD (did not reform); Saijah carried the rapier out.

